After investigation, this issue is caused by the following update function:

{code}
int pubIpSet(ccInstance * inst, void *ip)
{
    if (!ip || !inst) {
        return (1);
    }

    if ((strcmp(inst->state, "Pending") && strcmp(inst->state, "Extant"))) {
        snprintf(inst->ccnet.publicIp, IP_BUFFER_SIZE, "0.0.0.0");
        return (0);
    }

    LOGDEBUG("pubIpSet(): set: %s/%s\n", inst->ccnet.publicIp, (char *)ip);
    snprintf(inst->ccnet.publicIp, IP_BUFFER_SIZE, "%s", (char *)ip);
    return (0);
}
{code}

There seem to be a race condition where the terminate, describe and unassign seems to be out of order. Basically, because of potential instance restoration on CC, this is considered OK and I already validated that the IP gets re-assigned on new instances and that CLC ignores these IP assignation when CC reports teardown
